title.narrative: Government and partner capacities to respond to nutrition in humanitarian crises strengthened

description.narrative: UNICEF through the Emergency Nutrition Coordination Unit (ENCU, Nutrition Cluster) supported the GoE in developing and implementing multiple emergency nutrition responses for complex crises across the country. In addition, UNICEF ensured a robust coordination of emergency nutrition response at national and sub-national levels through ENCU.UNICEF advocacy resulted in an improved understanding of the GoE and donor community on the importance of nutrition resilience. UNICEF contributed to improved capacity of the FoH, National Disaster Risk Management Commission (NDRMC) and partner NGOs in responding to emergencies, through organizing a training on Nutrition in Emergencies and following up on the implantation. | Status:Met | As-of Date:30/06/2020
